Ex. 1 :- The function provided is broken. Your job is to figure out what's going on and fix it.

def append_elem_to_list(a_list, an_elem):
    # THIS IS BROKEN
    # YOUR JOB IS TO FIX IT
    # You can change this function as much as you want
    a_list.add(an_elem)
    return a_list


Solution :- 

def append_elem_to_list(a_list, an_elem):
    
    a_list.append(an_elem)
    return a_list
